# Java & Spring Boot Rules

## Language
- Java 17 — use `record`, sealed classes, text blocks, pattern matching where appropriate
- Prefer `Optional` over `null` returns in domain layer
- Use `@NonNull` / `@Nullable` (Jakarta) on public method params

## Spring Boot
- `@SpringBootApplication` only on main class — no scanning hacks
- `@ConfigurationProperties` for typed config — no `@Value` string injection
- Profiles: `default` (local H2), `docker`, `prod`

## DO ✅
```java
// Constructor injection with final fields
@Service
public class OrderApplicationService {
    private final OrderRepository orderRepository;
    private final EventPublisher eventPublisher;

    public OrderApplicationService(OrderRepository orderRepository,
                                   EventPublisher eventPublisher) {
        this.orderRepository = orderRepository;
        this.eventPublisher = eventPublisher;
    }
}

// Immutable DTO as record
public record CreateOrderRequest(
    @NotBlank String customerId,
    @NotEmpty List<OrderItemRequest> items
) {}
```

## DON'T ❌
```java
// Field injection
@Autowired
private OrderRepository orderRepository;  // ❌ never

// Mutable DTO
public class CreateOrderRequest {
    private String customerId;  // ❌ use record instead
    public void setCustomerId(String id) { ... }
}
```

## Naming Conventions
| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Domain entity | `PascalCase` | `Order`, `PaymentTransaction` |
| Value object | `PascalCase` | `Money`, `OrderId` |
| DTO | `{Action}{Entity}Request/Response` | `CreateOrderRequest` |
| Event | `{Entity}{PastTense}Event` | `OrderCreatedEvent` |
| Repository interface | `{Entity}Repository` | `OrderRepository` |
| JPA entity | `{Entity}JpaEntity` | `OrderJpaEntity` |

## Checklist before PR
- [ ] No `@Autowired` on fields
- [ ] All DTOs are `record`
- [ ] Domain classes have zero Spring imports
- [ ] No business logic in `@RestController`
- [ ] MapStruct mapper exists for every JPA↔domain mapping
